article_title: Contra White House, Obamacare Exchanges Enroll Roughly 5 Million Uninsured, Not 11.4 Million

article_metadata.author: The Apothecary

og.description: Last night, the White House tweeted that “about 11.4 million Americans are signed up for private health coverage” through Obamacare’s insurance exchanges. President Obama claims that this figure proves that his health law is working. But once you unravel the spin, what the latest numbers show is that the pace of enrollment in Obamacare’s exchanges has slowed down by more than half. If previous trends hold, Obamacare exchanges have enrolled approximately more than 5 million previously uninsured individuals: a far cry from 11.4 million.
